                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/235</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-06T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department is informed that on February 18 Federal troops fired on the residence
                    of W. W. Craib, at the Jatibonico plant of The Cuba Company, while there were
                    sheltered there British and American women and children.</p>
                <p>You will investigate and report fully by cable to the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
